title.rendered: Sri Lanka vs Australia, Women’s T20 World Cup 2023: Today’s Match Preview, Fantasy Cricket Tips

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on the recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable XIs

Sri Lanka: Chamari Athapaththu (c), Harshitha Madavi Samarawickrama, Vishmi Gunarathne, Nilakshi de Silva, Anushka Sanjeewani (wk), Oshadi Ranasinghe, Kavisha Dilhari, Ama Kanchana, Sugandika Kumari, Inoka Ranaweera, Achini Kulasuriya

Australia: Alyssa Healy (wk), Beth Mooney, Meg Lanning (c), Ashleigh Gardner, Ellyse Perry, Grace Harris, Tahlia McGrath, Georgia Wareham, Alana King/Jess Jonassen, Megan Schutt, Darcie Brown

Pitch Report

Venue: St George’s Park, Port Elizabeth

In the only women’s T20I played at the venue, Australia beat Bangladesh by 8 wickets.

1st innings score: 107

2nd innings score: 111

Wickets per innings: 4.5

Type: Good for spin

Wins

Batting 1st: —

Batting 2nd: 100%

Fantasy Tips of The Day

Alyssa Healy averages 56 against Sri Lanka. To fuel the fire, her career-best of 148 came against the same opposition.

Beth Mooney averages 63 against Sri Lanka, including a century.

Chamari Athapaththu is the highest run-scorer (251) in the T20Is involving these sides. She is also the leading wicket-taker (4) for Sri Lanka against Australia.

Inoka Ranaweera has not gone wicketless in her last 10 competitive T20s, overall scalping 19.

Meg Lanning has generated a 30-run bonus in consecutive matches. Against Sri Lanka, she has top scores of 56* and 41* in four innings.

Ashleigh Gardner provides points with both bat and ball. Besides being the leading wicket-taker (6) in the tournament, she bats at No.4.

As many as four players from Sri Lanka have been a part of the Best11 in four of the last five games: Anushka Sanjeewani, Kavisha Dilhari, Inoka, and Nilakshi de Silva.

Georgia Wareham, the vice-captain of the Best11 in the last game, has not gone wicketless for eight consecutive games.
